@node "Document_0" "INTRODUCTION"
@next "Document_1"
@prev "Main"

 What Is FileBaseUpdate?
 ***********************

    FileBaseUpdate is a CNet4.x @{b}dos@{ub} based utility to update CNet's internal
size and postdate of an item within a file subboard.

 Why Is This Needed?
 *******************

    I run automated processes which update certian files on a regular basis.
These include filelists, aminet indexes and a few other files.  Unfortunatly,
CNet only knows the filesize and postdate from the origional adoption into the
subboard.  I needed a way for my users to know if a list had been updated or
not.... The result was FileBaseUpdate.

 What Can/Can't FileBaseUpdate Do?
 *********************************

    FileBaseUpdate @{b}only changes the size and post date of an item@{ub}, it does
will not make the item appear on NS lists, nor will it change the items purge
date.
@endnode

@node "Document_1" "   USAGE    "
@next "Document_2"
@prev "Document_0"
 How Do I Use This Program?
 **************************

    FileBaseUpdate is a @{b}DOS@{ub} based program, meaning it @{b}MUST@{ub} be started from the
cli.  It takes two possible arguments:

        Physical Subboard #  - Specifies a single subboard to process

        ALL                  - Globally scans all file bases

    Example:

        FileBaseUpdate 216

            This will update only subboard number 216

        FileBaseUpdate ALL

            Will process every file subboard
@endnode

